Both residual and recurrent cholesteatomas are designated
as cholesteatoma recidivism (CR) in this study. Residual
disease is defined as persistence of cholesteatoma following an incomplete removal. Recurrent cholesteatoma is a newly developed cholesteatoma, usually secondary to a retraction pocket extending into the attic, antrum, mesotympanum, eustachian tube, facial recess.
